    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-05-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="397"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Office U. S. Military Telegraph</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">War Department, Washington, D. C.,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-05-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 18, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Orders have been given for the arrest and punishment of the fabricators and
                    publishers of the spurious proclamation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">U.
                            S. Minister Plenipotentiary, London, England.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>[Copy to Hon. William L. Dayton, U. S. minister plenipotentiary, Paris.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
